modules.description: Provides operations for manipulating elements of a commutative group, including addition, subtraction, and conversion to and from S-expression representations. Works with the abstract type `t` that represents group elements. Used to handle algebraic structures where operations are commutative and invertible, such as integer arithmetic or modular operations.

Provides vector addition, subtraction, and scalar multiplication operations on a type `t`, along with S-expression serialization and deserialization. Works with a generic vector-like data structure represented by `t`. Used for mathematical computations in physics simulations and geometric transformations.

Performs group and ring operations including addition, multiplication, and inverse computation on finite fields and modular integers. Works with custom types for field elements and polynomial structures over prime fields. Enables cryptographic calculations such as discrete logarithm approximations and polynomial factorization.

Combines group operations and vector arithmetic into a unified framework for algebraic computations. Supports addition, subtraction, and scalar multiplication on abstract types `t`, with serialization to and from S-expressions. Enables handling of integer-based groups and vector spaces in applications like physics and geometry. Examples include adding group elements, scaling vectors, and converting structures to and from textual representations.
